Phase 2/6 complete. **51 tests pass, 0 warnings, 0 failures.**

### Summary of what was implemented:

**`src/lexer.rs`** — Full lexer ported from `go/lexer/lexer.go` + `go/lexer/shebang.go`
- `Lexer` struct with all internal methods: `read_ident`, `read_string`, `read_text_block`, `read_number`, `read_hex`, `read_operator`, `read_comparison`, `read_dollar`, `read_shebang`, `read_comment`
- Public API: `tokenize()`, `parse_shebang()`, `parse_compact_line()`
- Handles shebang `#!...`, compact config `#!compact ...`, comments, escape sequences, hex/float numbers, `$VAR`/`${VAR}`/`$(CMD)` interpolation markers
- Collapses consecutive newlines
- 18 tests

**`src/parser.rs`** — Full parser ported from `go/parser/parser.go`
- `Parser` struct with all parsing methods: script-level (shebang, compact config, background `&`), statements (if/else-if/else, for/in, while, fn, do/with/using/in/compact, try/eval/fail/accept/partial/upto, within, wait, exec, print, exit, env, include, compact, return, break, continue, block, var assign, fn call), expressions (binary precedence climbing, unary, literals, var ref, command subst, file path `@`, group, array, index)
- **Index access parsed inside `parse_binary_expr`** (right after `parse_primary`) for correct precedence: `"prefix" + arr[0]` parses as `"prefix" + (arr[0])`
- Precedence levels: `or`(1) < `and`(2) < `==`, `!=`, `<`, `>`, `<=`, `>=`(3) < `+`, `-`(4) < `*`, `/`(5)
- Public API: `parse()`, `parse_str()`
- 16 tests

**`src/interpolation.rs`** — Interpolation resolver ported from `go/eval/evaluator.go`
- `Interpolation::resolve()` — regex-based `${VAR}` and `$(CMD)` resolution with `\$` escaping
- `Interpolation::resolve_spans()` — resolution of pre-parsed `InterpSpan` nodes
- 8 tests

