# Todos
[✓] Fix resolve_interpolations to fall back to regex-based Interpolation::resolve() when interps is empty
[✓] Update tests to verify regex-based string interpolation works
[✓] Run cargo build and cargo test to verify fix

**Fix applied.** The root cause: `resolve_interpolations()` in `src/eval.rs:213` returned the raw string unchanged when `interps` was empty, skipping interpolation resolution entirely. The Go reference always falls back to regex-based `${VAR}`/`$(cmd)` resolution via `resolveInterpolations()`.

**Changes:**

1. **`src/eval.rs:213-238`** — `resolve_interpolations` now calls `Interpolation::resolve_spans()` when `interps` is non-empty (as before), but falls back to `Interpolation::resolve()` (regex-based) when `interps` is empty, matching the Go `evaluator.go` behavior.

2. **`src/eval.rs:592`** — Fixed `test_string_interpolation_escape` assertion: `\$` correctly resolves to `$` (the backslash escapes the dollar sign), matching both the test's own comment and the Go reference.

