All tasks complete. Here's a summary of changes:

**`src/eval.rs`** — Added 8 new evaluator methods:
- `eval_agent_call` — dispatches agent calls via engine registry or falls back to CLI
- `eval_binary_try` — retry loop with truthy check and optional fail block
- `eval_eval_try` — evaluated retry with stdout capture to `$report`, accept/partial/fail blocks
- `eval_wait` — parallel thread spawning for block statements + joining bg handles
- `eval_background` — fire-and-forget thread, pushes handle to `bg_handles`
- `eval_include` — reads file, tokenizes, parses, evaluates in current scope
- `eval_dir_block` — saves/restores current dir around body evaluation
- `eval_compact_stmt` — parses and applies compact directives

**`src/eval.rs`** — Structural changes:
- Added `bg_handles: Arc<Mutex<Vec<JoinHandle<()>>>>` field
- Wired all 8 new node types in `eval_statement` dispatch
- `eval_print` now returns the message value (matching Go semantics)
- `eval_command_subst` trims whitespace from output

**`src/scope.rs`** — Fixed `set()` to always propagate new variables up to the root scope (matching Go's scope semantics)

**Tests:** 8 new unit tests + all 99 existing pass; `test_all.ash` exits 0 with all sections green.

